('grain',
 'Grain',
 'AI meeting recorder that clips, highlights, and shares key moments from video calls',
 'Grain is an AI meeting recorder that focuses on making insights from video calls shareable and actionable, not just stored. During a meeting, Grain automatically transcribes and records the conversation. After the meeting, AI identifies key moments, generates a summary, and lets users clip specific segments into short video highlights that can be shared directly in Slack, Notion, or via link. Sales teams use Grain to clip customer objections, product managers use it to capture user research insights, and managers use it to share performance feedback without requiring everyone to watch the full recording. The workflow is closer to video editing than traditional note-taking - individual moments are treated as standalone content worth sharing, not just timestamps in a long transcript. Grain integrates with Salesforce and HubSpot, automatically syncing call summaries and key moments to contact and deal records. The free plan allows unlimited recordings with a 10-hour storage limit.',
 NULL,
 'https://grain.com',
