 ARRAY['Less suitable as a full conversation intelligence platform like Gong', 'Clip-first workflow requires more active curation than auto-summary tools', 'Storage limits on lower plans can fill quickly for heavy recording users'],
 ARRAY['Sales call coaching and key moment sharing', 'User research session highlight reels', 'Customer insight library for product teams']),

('read-ai',
 'Read AI',
 'AI meeting copilot with real-time summaries, engagement scores, and action items',
 'Read AI is an AI meeting assistant that analyses meetings in real time, producing summaries, action items, and engagement metrics as the conversation unfolds. Unlike tools that only process recordings after a meeting ends, Read AI provides a live summary and action item list that updates throughout the call, so participants can confirm shared understanding before disconnecting. The engagement scoring feature analyses speaking time, sentiment, and participation patterns to give meeting organisers visibility into which meetings are draining versus energising their teams. Read AI works across Zoom, Google Meet, and Microsoft Teams without requiring a bot to join the call - it processes audio directly. The reports include a meeting score, executive summary, questions asked, decisions made, and a full transcript. For leadership teams running many back-to-back meetings, Read AI is one of the few tools that gives data on whether meetings are actually productive rather than just captured.',
 NULL,
 'https://read.ai',
